===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any day of the week except Sunday and often also Saturday.<ref>[http://www.yourdictionary.com/weekday American Heritage]</ref><ref>[http://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/weekday Collins]</ref><ref>[http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/weekday Merriam-Webster]</ref>
#: In countries with a six-day [[workweek]] (including all countries in the past), the weekdays are the same as the [[workday]]s ([[working day]]s). In countries with a five-day workweek, the term ''weekday'' sometimes has the old meaning "all days except Sunday" and sometimes refers to "all days except Saturday and Sunday".

